detailedViolations.description: Ensure each HTML document contains a non-empty <title> element
detailedViolations.help: Documents must have <title> element to aid in navigation

nodes.failureSummary:
Fix any of the following:
  Document does not have a non-empty <title> element

detailedViolations.description: Ensure that the page, or at least one of its frames contains a level-one heading
detailedViolations.help: Page should contain a level-one heading

nodes.failureSummary:
Fix all of the following:
  Page must have a level-one heading

detailedViolations.description: The title element in the head section should be non-empty.
detailedViolations.help: Ensure accessibility compliance for this element.

nodes.failureSummary: Fix: Review element and ensure it meets accessibility guidelines.

issues.message: The title element in the head section should be non-empty.

detailedViolations.help: The title gives screen reader users an overview of the page, and search engine users rely on it heavily to determine if a page is relevant to their search. [Learn more about document titles](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/4.9/document-title).

nodes.failureSummary: Fix: Document doesn't have a `<title>` element

details.message: Keyboard navigation test completed (with demo violations)

violations.description: Interactive element lacks visible focus indicator
violations.help: All interactive elements must have a visible focus indicator when focused via keyboard navigation.

nodes.failureSummary: Fix: Add CSS focus styles for button element: "outline: 2px solid #0078d4" or similar.
